Bilateral simultaneous rupture of the infrapatellar tendon in a recreational athlete. A case report.
 Bilateral rupture of the infrapatellar tendons is a rare event in an otherwise healthy athletic individual.
 The event is usually quite severe and diagnosis can be readily made on a clinical examination.
 In the case presented here, predisposing factors consisted of an underlying patella alta and a long history of repetitive trauma to the knee.
 Prompt diagnosis and surgical repair will lead to a good functional result.
